{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c9684ef1-13c8-4a0d-a0de-878684d73073","content":"With xUnit v3 + MTP, the VSTest `--filter` syntax doesn't apply. MTP uses **`--treenode-filter`** with a path-based syntax instead.\n\n**Old (VSTest):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**New (MTP):**\n```\ndotnet test -- --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*/**[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\n**Breakdown of the translation:**\n\n| VSTest filter | MTP treenode-filter |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*/**` (glob match on the test tree path) |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (trait predicate on matched nodes) |\n| `&` (AND) | Combined — the predicate `[...]` applies to the path it's attached to |\n\nThe `--` separator tells `dotnet test` to pass the argument through to the underlying MTP runner. You can also run the built executable directly:\n\n```\n./bin/Debug/net8.0/TestProject --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*/**[Category=Smoke]\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c0ad9c56-4537-4cda-a8b6-2910af36c680","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3 with MTP (Microsoft Testing Platform). They have `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner` set to true.\n\nKey changes:\n1. With MTP, the filter syntax changes. `dotnet test --filter` uses VSTest filter syntax, but with MTP the runner is different.\n2. In xUnit v3 with MTP, `dotnet test` still works but the filter syntax for MTP is different.\n3. With MTP, the executable itself is the test runner, so you can run it directly.\n\nLet me think about the filter translation:\n\n\nThe old filter `\"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"` uses VSTest syntax where the tilde means \"contains\" and the ampersand combines conditions. With MTP, the filter syntax is different from VSTest, so I need to figure out how to translate this when using `dotnet test` with the MTP runner.\n\nWhen `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`, `dotnet test` delegates to MTP, which uses its own filter engine. The property names and semantics change—`FullyQualifiedName` might not work the same way, and traits are exposed differently. For xUnit v3 with MTP, I should use `--treenode-filter` for native MTP filtering or adjust the `--filter` syntax to use MTP's property names and path notation.\n\nWriting filter examples... The key difference is that VSTest's `--filter` syntax isn't automatically converted to MTP's treenode filter format, so I need to use `--treenode-filter` directly with the glob pattern syntax instead. When running through `dotnet test`, I can pass it via `--` to forward arguments to the underlying runner, or run the test executable directly with the filter option.","outputTokens":1426,"requestId":"7C31:26FA86:14B2AEA:173F6D3:69F942AB"},"id":"9c7af67d-d99a-43ad-822e-55396f387779","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:07:19.306Z","parentId":"f1f270c3-b315-43e5-9c10-b7db07d5ac08"}
